Here's a quickie little shell/awk script which will help in identifying the
largest files in and under a given directory.  I've found it really good at
ferreting out monstrous, forgotten files under my account (and those of
other users sharing my disk partition :-) ).  I've tested this only on SysV;
please let me know of any fixes needed for BSD.

